00176 /* 
00177    Flags/methods for returning states.
00178    
00179    The swig conversion methods, as ConvertPtr, return and integer 
00180    that tells if the conversion was successful or not. And if not,
00181    an error code can be returned (see swigerrors.swg for the codes).
00182    
00183    Use the following macros/flags to set or process the returning
00184    states.
00185    
00186    In old swig versions, you usually write code as:
00187 
00188      if (SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags) != -1) {
00189        // success code
00190      } else {
00191        //fail code
00192      }
00193 
00194    Now you can be more explicit as:
00195 
00196     int res = SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags);
00197     if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
00198       // success code
00199     } else {
00200       // fail code
00201     }
00202 
00203    that seems to be the same, but now you can also do
00204 
00205     Type *ptr;
00206     int res = SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,(void **)(&ptr),ty.flags);
00207     if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
00208       // success code
00209       if (SWIG_IsNewObj(res) {
00210         ...
00211     delete *ptr;
00212       } else {
00213         ...
00214       }
00215     } else {
00216       // fail code
00217     }
00218     
00219    I.e., now SWIG_ConvertPtr can return new objects and you can
00220    identify the case and take care of the deallocation. Of course that
00221    requires also to SWIG_ConvertPtr to return new result values, as
00222 
00223       int SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj, ptr,...) {         
00224         if (<obj is ok>) {                 
00225           if (<need new object>) {             
00226             *ptr = <ptr to new allocated object>; 
00227             return SWIG_NEWOBJ;            
00228           } else {                     
00229             *ptr = <ptr to old object>;        
00230             return SWIG_OLDOBJ;            
00231           }                        
00232         } else {                       
00233           return SWIG_BADOBJ;              
00234         }                          
00235       }
00236 
00237    Of course, returning the plain '0(success)/-1(fail)' still works, but you can be
00238    more explicit by returning SWIG_BADOBJ, SWIG_ERROR or any of the
00239    swig errors code.
00240 
00241    Finally, if the SWIG_CASTRANK_MODE is enabled, the result code
00242    allows to return the 'cast rank', for example, if you have this
00243 
00244        int food(double)
00245        int fooi(int);
00246 
00247    and you call
00248  
00249       food(1)   // cast rank '1'  (1 -> 1.0)
00250       fooi(1)   // cast rank '0'
00251 
00252    just use the SWIG_AddCast()/SWIG_CheckState()
00253 
00254 
00255  */
00256 #define SWIG_OK                    (0) 
00257 #define SWIG_ERROR                 (-1)
00258 #define SWIG_IsOK(r)               (r >= 0)
00259 #define SWIG_ArgError(r)           ((r != SWIG_ERROR) ? r : SWIG_TypeError)  
00260 
00261 /* The CastRankLimit says how many bits are used for the cast rank */
00262 #define SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT         (1 << 8)
00263 /* The NewMask denotes the object was created (using new/malloc) */
00264 #define SWIG_NEWOBJMASK            (SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT  << 1)
00265 /* The TmpMask is for in/out typemaps that use temporal objects */
00266 #define SWIG_TMPOBJMASK            (SWIG_NEWOBJMASK << 1)
00267 /* Simple returning values */
00268 #define SWIG_BADOBJ                (SWIG_ERROR)
00269 #define SWIG_OLDOBJ                (SWIG_OK)
00270 #define SWIG_NEWOBJ                (SWIG_OK | SWIG_NEWOBJMASK)
00271 #define SWIG_TMPOBJ                (SWIG_OK | SWIG_TMPOBJMASK)
00272 /* Check, add and del mask methods */
00273 #define SWIG_AddNewMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r | SWIG_NEWOBJMASK) : r)
00274 #define SWIG_DelNewMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r & ~SWIG_NEWOBJMASK) : r)
00275 #define SWIG_IsNewObj(r)           (SWIG_IsOK(r) && (r & SWIG_NEWOBJMASK))
00276 #define SWIG_AddTmpMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r | SWIG_TMPOBJMASK) : r)
00277 #define SWIG_DelTmpMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r & ~SWIG_TMPOBJMASK) : r)
00278 #define SWIG_IsTmpObj(r)           (SWIG_IsOK(r) && (r & SWIG_TMPOBJMASK))

00283 #  ifndef SWIG_TypeRank
00284 #    define SWIG_TypeRank             unsigned long
00285 #  endif
00286 #  ifndef SWIG_MAXCASTRANK            /* Default cast allowed */
00287 #    define SWIG_MAXCASTRANK          (2)
00288 #  endif
00289 #  define SWIG_CASTRANKMASK          ((SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT) -1)
00290 #  define SWIG_CastRank(r)           (r & SWIG_CASTRANKMASK)
00291 SWIGINTERNINLINE int SWIG_AddCast(int r) { 
00292   return SWIG_IsOK(r) ? ((SWIG_CastRank(r) < SWIG_MAXCASTRANK) ? (r + 1) : SWIG_ERROR) : r;

00332 /* Structure used to store module information
00333  * Each module generates one structure like this, and the runtime collects
00334  * all of these structures and stores them in a circularly linked list.*/
00335 typedef struct swig_module_info {
00336   swig_type_info         **types;       /* Array of pointers to swig_type_info structures that are in this module */
00337   size_t                 size;              /* Number of types in this module */
00338   struct swig_module_info *next;        /* Pointer to next element in circularly linked list */
00339   swig_type_info         **type_initial;    /* Array of initially generated type structures */

00344 /* 
00345   Compare two type names skipping the space characters, therefore
00346   "char*" == "char *" and "Class<int>" == "Class<int >", etc.
00347 
00348   Return 0 when the two name types are equivalent, as in
00349   strncmp, but skipping ' '.
00350 */
00351 SWIGRUNTIME int
00352 SWIG_TypeNameComp(const char *f1, const char *l1,
00353           const char *f2, const char *l2) {
00354   for (;(f1 != l1) && (f2 != l2); ++f1, ++f2) {
00355     while ((*f1 == ' ') && (f1 != l1)) ++f1;
00356     while ((*f2 == ' ') && (f2 != l2)) ++f2;
00357     if (*f1 != *f2) return (*f1 > *f2) ? 1 : -1;
00358   }
00359   return (int)((l1 - f1) - (l2 - f2));
00360 }

00362 /*
00363   Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...
00364   Return 0 if not equal, 1 if equal
00365 */
00366 SWIGRUNTIME int
00367 SWIG_TypeEquiv(const char *nb, const char *tb) {
00368   int equiv = 0;
00369   const char* te = tb + strlen(tb);
00370   const char* ne = nb;
00371   while (!equiv && *ne) {
00372     for (nb = ne; *ne; ++ne) {
00373       if (*ne == '|') break;
00374     }
00375     equiv = (SWIG_TypeNameComp(nb, ne, tb, te) == 0) ? 1 : 0;
00376     if (*ne) ++ne;
00377   }
00378   return equiv;
00379 }
00380 
00381 /*
00382   Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...
00383   Return 0 if equal, -1 if nb < tb, 1 if nb > tb
00384 */
00385 SWIGRUNTIME int
00386 SWIG_TypeCompare(const char *nb, const char *tb) {
00387   int equiv = 0;
00388   const char* te = tb + strlen(tb);
00389   const char* ne = nb;
00390   while (!equiv && *ne) {
00391     for (nb = ne; *ne; ++ne) {
00392       if (*ne == '|') break;
00393     }
00394     equiv = (SWIG_TypeNameComp(nb, ne, tb, te) == 0) ? 1 : 0;
00395     if (*ne) ++ne;
00396   }
00397   return equiv;
00398 }

00401 /* think of this as a c++ template<> or a scheme macro */
00402 #define SWIG_TypeCheck_Template(comparison, ty)         \
00403   if (ty) {                                             \
00404     swig_cast_info *iter = ty->cast;                    \
00405     while (iter) {                                      \
00406       if (comparison) {                                 \
00407         if (iter == ty->cast) return iter;              \
00408         /* Move iter to the top of the linked list */   \
00409         iter->prev->next = iter->next;                  \
00410         if (iter->next)                                 \
00411           iter->next->prev = iter->prev;                \
00412         iter->next = ty->cast;                          \
00413         iter->prev = 0;                                 \
00414         if (ty->cast) ty->cast->prev = iter;            \
00415         ty->cast = iter;                                \
00416         return iter;                                    \
00417       }                                                 \
00418       iter = iter->next;                                \
00419     }                                                   \
00420   }                                                     \
00421   return 0
00422

00424   Check the typename
00425 */
00426 SWIGRUNTIME swig_cast_info *
00427 SWIG_TypeCheck(const char *c, swig_type_info *ty) {
00428   SWIG_TypeCheck_Template(strcmp(iter->type->name, c) == 0, ty);

00433 SWIG_TypeCheckStruct(swig_type_info *from, swig_type_info *into) {

00437 /*
00438   Cast a pointer up an inheritance hierarchy
00439 */
00440 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE void *
00441 SWIG_TypeCast(swig_cast_info *ty, void *ptr, int *newmemory) {
00442   return ((!ty) || (!ty->converter)) ? ptr : (*ty->converter)(ptr, newmemory);
00443 }

00445 /* 
00446    Dynamic pointer casting. Down an inheritance hierarchy
00447 */
00448 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00449 SWIG_TypeDynamicCast(swig_type_info *ty, void **ptr) {
00450   swig_type_info *lastty = ty;
00451   if (!ty || !ty->dcast) return ty;
00452   while (ty && (ty->dcast)) {
00453     ty = (*ty->dcast)(ptr);
00454     if (ty) lastty = ty;
00455   }
00456   return lastty;
00457 }

00467 /*
00468   Return the pretty name associated with this type,
00469   that is an unmangled type name in a form presentable to the user.
00470 */
00471 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00472 SWIG_TypePrettyName(const swig_type_info *type) {
00473   /* The "str" field contains the equivalent pretty names of the
00474      type, separated by vertical-bar characters.  We choose
00475      to print the last name, as it is often (?) the most
00476      specific. */
00477   if (!type) return NULL;
00478   if (type->str != NULL) {
00479     const char *last_name = type->str;
00480     const char *s;
00481     for (s = type->str; *s; s++)
00482       if (*s == '|') last_name = s+1;
00483     return last_name;
00484   }
00485   else
00486     return type->name;
00487 }

00489 /* 
00490    Set the clientdata field for a type
00491 */
00492 SWIGRUNTIME void
00493 SWIG_TypeClientData(swig_type_info *ti, void *clientdata) {
00494   swig_cast_info *cast = ti->cast;
00495   /* if (ti->clientdata == clientdata) return; */
00496   ti->clientdata = clientdata;
00497   
00498   while (cast) {
00499     if (!cast->converter) {
00500       swig_type_info *tc = cast->type;
00501       if (!tc->clientdata) {
00502     SWIG_TypeClientData(tc, clientdata);
00503       }
00504     }    
00505     cast = cast->next;
00506   }
00507 }
00508 SWIGRUNTIME void
00509 SWIG_TypeNewClientData(swig_type_info *ti, void *clientdata) {
00510   SWIG_TypeClientData(ti, clientdata);
00511   ti->owndata = 1;
00512 }

00514 /*
00515   Search for a swig_type_info structure only by mangled name
00516   Search is a O(log #types)
00517   
00518   We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.  
00519   Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around
00520   the circular list.
00521 */
00522 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00523 SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start, 
00524                             swig_module_info *end, 
00525                     const char *name) {
00526   swig_module_info *iter = start;
00527   do {
00528     if (iter->size) {
00529       register size_t l = 0;
00530       register size_t r = iter->size - 1;
00531       do {
00532     /* since l+r >= 0, we can (>> 1) instead (/ 2) */
00533     register size_t i = (l + r) >> 1; 
00534     const char *iname = iter->types[i]->name;
00535     if (iname) {
00536       register int compare = strcmp(name, iname);
00537       if (compare == 0) {       
00538         return iter->types[i];
00539       } else if (compare < 0) {
00540         if (i) {
00541           r = i - 1;
00542         } else {
00543           break;
00544         }
00545       } else if (compare > 0) {
00546         l = i + 1;
00547       }
00548     } else {
00549       break; /* should never happen */
00550     }
00551       } while (l <= r);
00552     }
00553     iter = iter->next;
00554   } while (iter != end);
00555   return 0;
00556 }
00557 
00558 /*
00559   Search for a swig_type_info structure for either a mangled name or a human readable name.
00560   It first searches the mangled names of the types, which is a O(log #types)
00561   If a type is not found it then searches the human readable names, which is O(#types).
00562   
00563   We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.  
00564   Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around
00565   the circular list.
00566 */
00567 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00568 SWIG_TypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start, 
00569                      swig_module_info *end, 
00570              const char *name) {
00571   /* STEP 1: Search the name field using binary search */
00572   swig_type_info *ret = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(start, end, name);
00573   if (ret) {
00574     return ret;
00575   } else {
00576     /* STEP 2: If the type hasn't been found, do a complete search
00577        of the str field (the human readable name) */
00578     swig_module_info *iter = start;
00579     do {
00580       register size_t i = 0;
00581       for (; i < iter->size; ++i) {
00582     if (iter->types[i]->str && (SWIG_TypeEquiv(iter->types[i]->str, name)))
00583       return iter->types[i];
00584       }
00585       iter = iter->next;
00586     } while (iter != end);
00587   }
00588   
00589   /* neither found a match */
00590   return 0;
00591 }

00593 /* 
00594    Pack binary data into a string
00595 */
00596 SWIGRUNTIME char *
00597 SWIG_PackData(char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz) {
00598   static const char hex[17] = "0123456789abcdef";
00599   register const unsigned char *u = (unsigned char *) ptr;
00600   register const unsigned char *eu =  u + sz;
00601   for (; u != eu; ++u) {
00602     register unsigned char uu = *u;
00603     *(c++) = hex[(uu & 0xf0) >> 4];
00604     *(c++) = hex[uu & 0xf];
00605   }
00606   return c;
00607 }
00608 
00609 /* 
00610    Unpack binary data from a string
00611 */
00612 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00613 SWIG_UnpackData(const char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz) {
00614   register unsigned char *u = (unsigned char *) ptr;
00615   register const unsigned char *eu = u + sz;
00616   for (; u != eu; ++u) {
00617     register char d = *(c++);
00618     register unsigned char uu;
00619     if ((d >= '0') && (d <= '9'))
00620       uu = ((d - '0') << 4);
00621     else if ((d >= 'a') && (d <= 'f'))
00622       uu = ((d - ('a'-10)) << 4);
00623     else 
00624       return (char *) 0;
00625     d = *(c++);
00626     if ((d >= '0') && (d <= '9'))
00627       uu |= (d - '0');
00628     else if ((d >= 'a') && (d <= 'f'))
00629       uu |= (d - ('a'-10));
00630     else 
00631       return (char *) 0;
00632     *u = uu;
00633   }
00634   return c;
00635 }
00636 
00637 /* 
00638    Pack 'void *' into a string buffer.
00639 */
00640 SWIGRUNTIME char *
00641 SWIG_PackVoidPtr(char *buff, void *ptr, const char *name, size_t bsz) {
00642   char *r = buff;
00643   if ((2*sizeof(void *) + 2) > bsz) return 0;
00644   *(r++) = '_';
00645   r = SWIG_PackData(r,&ptr,sizeof(void *));
00646   if (strlen(name) + 1 > (bsz - (r - buff))) return 0;
00647   strcpy(r,name);
00648   return buff;
00649 }
00650 
00651 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00652 SWIG_UnpackVoidPtr(const char *c, void **ptr, const char *name) {
00653   if (*c != '_') {
00654     if (strcmp(c,"NULL") == 0) {
00655       *ptr = (void *) 0;
00656       return name;
00657     } else {
00658       return 0;
00659     }
00660   }
00661   return SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,sizeof(void *));
00662 }
00663 
00664 SWIGRUNTIME char *
00665 SWIG_PackDataName(char *buff, void *ptr, size_t sz, const char *name, size_t bsz) {
00666   char *r = buff;
00667   size_t lname = (name ? strlen(name) : 0);
00668   if ((2*sz + 2 + lname) > bsz) return 0;
00669   *(r++) = '_';
00670   r = SWIG_PackData(r,ptr,sz);
00671   if (lname) {
00672     strncpy(r,name,lname+1);
00673   } else {
00674     *r = 0;
00675   }
00676   return buff;
00677 }
00678 
00679 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00680 SWIG_UnpackDataName(const char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz, const char *name) {
00681   if (*c != '_') {
00682     if (strcmp(c,"NULL") == 0) {
00683       memset(ptr,0,sz);
00684       return name;
00685     } else {
00686       return 0;
00687     }
00688   }
00689   return SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,sz);
00690 }

00730 static PyObject *
00731 PyString_FromFormat(const char *fmt, ...) {
00732   va_list ap;
00733   char buf[SWIG_PYBUFFER_SIZE * 2];
00734   int res;
00735   va_start(ap, fmt);
00736   res = vsnprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), fmt, ap);
00737   va_end(ap);
00738   return (res < 0 || res >= (int)sizeof(buf)) ? 0 : PyString_FromString(buf);
00739 }

00802 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
00803  * error manipulation
00804  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
00805 
00806 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject*
00807 SWIG_Python_ErrorType(int code) {
00808   PyObject* type = 0;
00809   switch(code) {
00810   case SWIG_MemoryError:
00811     type = PyExc_MemoryError;
00812     break;
00813   case SWIG_IOError:
00814     type = PyExc_IOError;
00815     break;
00816   case SWIG_RuntimeError:
00817     type = PyExc_RuntimeError;
00818     break;
00819   case SWIG_IndexError:
00820     type = PyExc_IndexError;
00821     break;
00822   case SWIG_TypeError:
00823     type = PyExc_TypeError;
00824     break;
00825   case SWIG_DivisionByZero:
00826     type = PyExc_ZeroDivisionError;
00827     break;
00828   case SWIG_OverflowError:
00829     type = PyExc_OverflowError;
00830     break;
00831   case SWIG_SyntaxError:
00832     type = PyExc_SyntaxError;
00833     break;
00834   case SWIG_ValueError:
00835     type = PyExc_ValueError;
00836     break;
00837   case SWIG_SystemError:
00838     type = PyExc_SystemError;
00839     break;
00840   case SWIG_AttributeError:
00841     type = PyExc_AttributeError;
00842     break;
00843   default:
00844     type = PyExc_RuntimeError;
00845   }
00846   return type;
00847 }

00849 
00850 SWIGRUNTIME void
00851 SWIG_Python_AddErrorMsg(const char* mesg)
00852 {
00853   PyObject *type = 0;
00854   PyObject *value = 0;
00855   PyObject *traceback = 0;
00856 
00857   if (PyErr_Occurred()) PyErr_Fetch(&type, &value, &traceback);
00858   if (value) {
00859     PyObject *old_str = PyObject_Str(value);
00860     PyErr_Clear();
00861     Py_XINCREF(type);
00862     PyErr_Format(type, "%s %s", PyString_AsString(old_str), mesg);
00863     Py_DECREF(old_str);
00864     Py_DECREF(value);
00865   } else {
00866     PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, mesg);
00867   }
00868 }

01058 /* Append a value to the result obj */
01059 
01060 SWIGINTERN PyObject*
01061 SWIG_Python_AppendOutput(PyObject* result, PyObject* obj) {
01062 #if !defined(SWIG_PYTHON_OUTPUT_TUPLE)
01063   if (!result) {
01064     result = obj;
01065   } else if (result == Py_None) {
01066     Py_DECREF(result);
01067     result = obj;
01068   } else {
01069     if (!PyList_Check(result)) {
01070       PyObject *o2 = result;
01071       result = PyList_New(1);
01072       PyList_SetItem(result, 0, o2);
01073     }
01074     PyList_Append(result,obj);
01075     Py_DECREF(obj);
01076   }
01077   return result;
01078 #else
01079   PyObject*   o2;
01080   PyObject*   o3;
01081   if (!result) {
01082     result = obj;
01083   } else if (result == Py_None) {
01084     Py_DECREF(result);
01085     result = obj;
01086   } else {
01087     if (!PyTuple_Check(result)) {
01088       o2 = result;
01089       result = PyTuple_New(1);
01090       PyTuple_SET_ITEM(result, 0, o2);
01091     }
01092     o3 = PyTuple_New(1);
01093     PyTuple_SET_ITEM(o3, 0, obj);
01094     o2 = result;
01095     result = PySequence_Concat(o2, o3);
01096     Py_DECREF(o2);
01097     Py_DECREF(o3);
01098   }
01099   return result;
01100 #endif
01101 }
01102 
01103 /* Unpack the argument tuple */
01104 
01105 SWIGINTERN int
01106 SWIG_Python_UnpackTuple(PyObject *args, const char *name, Py_ssize_t min, Py_ssize_t max, PyObject **objs)
01107 {
01108   if (!args) {
01109     if (!min && !max) {
01110       return 1;
01111     } else {
01112       PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "%s expected %s%d arguments, got none", 
01113            name, (min == max ? "" : "at least "), (int)min);
01114       return 0;
01115     }
01116   }  
01117   if (!PyTuple_Check(args)) {
01118     PyErr_SetString(PyExc_SystemError, "UnpackTuple() argument list is not a tuple");
01119     return 0;
01120   } else {
01121     register Py_ssize_t l = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args);
01122     if (l < min) {
01123       PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "%s expected %s%d arguments, got %d", 
01124            name, (min == max ? "" : "at least "), (int)min, (int)l);
01125       return 0;
01126     } else if (l > max) {
01127       PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "%s expected %s%d arguments, got %d", 
01128            name, (min == max ? "" : "at most "), (int)max, (int)l);
01129       return 0;
01130     } else {
01131       register int i;
01132       for (i = 0; i < l; ++i) {
01133     objs[i] = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, i);
01134       }
01135       for (; l < max; ++l) {
01136     objs[l] = 0;
01137       }
01138       return i + 1;
01139     }    
01140   }
01141 }

01233 
01234 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE PyObject *
01235 SWIG_Python_ExceptionType(swig_type_info *desc) {
01236   PySwigClientData *data = desc ? (PySwigClientData *) desc->clientdata : 0;
01237   PyObject *klass = data ? data->klass : 0;
01238   return (klass ? klass : PyExc_RuntimeError);
01239 }
01240 
01241 
01242 SWIGRUNTIME PySwigClientData * 
01243 PySwigClientData_New(PyObject* obj)
01244 {
01245   if (!obj) {
01246     return 0;
01247   } else {
01248     PySwigClientData *data = (PySwigClientData *)malloc(sizeof(PySwigClientData));
01249     /* the klass element */
01250     data->klass = obj;
01251     Py_INCREF(data->klass);
01252     /* the newraw method and newargs arguments used to create a new raw instance */
01253     if (PyClass_Check(obj)) {
01254       data->newraw = 0;
01255       data->newargs = obj;
01256       Py_INCREF(obj);
01257     } else {
01258 #if (PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x02020000)
01259       data->newraw = 0;
01260 #else
01261       data->newraw = PyObject_GetAttrString(data->klass, (char *)"__new__");
01262 #endif
01263       if (data->newraw) {
01264     Py_INCREF(data->newraw);
01265     data->newargs = PyTuple_New(1);
01266     PyTuple_SetItem(data->newargs, 0, obj);
01267       } else {
01268     data->newargs = obj;
01269       }
01270       Py_INCREF(data->newargs);
01271     }
01272     /* the destroy method, aka as the C++ delete method */
01273     data->destroy = PyObject_GetAttrString(data->klass, (char *)"__swig_destroy__");
01274     if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
01275       PyErr_Clear();
01276       data->destroy = 0;
01277     }
01278     if (data->destroy) {
01279       int flags;
01280       Py_INCREF(data->destroy);
01281       flags = PyCFunction_GET_FLAGS(data->destroy);
01282 #ifdef METH_O
01283       data->delargs = !(flags & (METH_O));
01284 #else
01285       data->delargs = 0;
01286 #endif
01287     } else {
01288       data->delargs = 0;
01289     }
01290     data->implicitconv = 0;
01291     return data;
01292   }
01293 }
01294 
01295 SWIGRUNTIME void 
01296 PySwigClientData_Del(PySwigClientData* data)
01297 {
01298   Py_XDECREF(data->newraw);
01299   Py_XDECREF(data->newargs);
01300   Py_XDECREF(data->destroy);
01301 }

01303 /* =============== PySwigObject =====================*/
01304 
01305 typedef struct {
01306   PyObject_HEAD
01307   void *ptr;
01308   swig_type_info *ty;
01309   int own;
01310   PyObject *next;
01311 } PySwigObject;
01312 
01313 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01314 PySwigObject_long(PySwigObject *v)
01315 {
01316   return PyLong_FromVoidPtr(v->ptr);
01317 }
01318 
01319 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01320 PySwigObject_format(const char* fmt, PySwigObject *v)
01321 {
01322   PyObject *res = NULL;
01323   PyObject *args = PyTuple_New(1);
01324   if (args) {
01325     if (PyTuple_SetItem(args, 0, PySwigObject_long(v)) == 0) {
01326       PyObject *ofmt = PyString_FromString(fmt);
01327       if (ofmt) {
01328     res = PyString_Format(ofmt,args);
01329     Py_DECREF(ofmt);
01330       }
01331       Py_DECREF(args);
01332     }
01333   }
01334   return res;
01335 }
01336 
01337 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01338 PySwigObject_oct(PySwigObject *v)
01339 {
01340   return PySwigObject_format("%o",v);
01341 }
01342 
01343 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01344 PySwigObject_hex(PySwigObject *v)
01345 {
01346   return PySwigObject_format("%x",v);
01347 }
01348 
01349 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01350 #ifdef METH_NOARGS
01351 PySwigObject_repr(PySwigObject *v)
01352 #else
01353 PySwigObject_repr(PySwigObject *v, PyObject *args)
01354 #endif
01355 {
01356   const char *name = SWIG_TypePrettyName(v->ty);
01357   PyObject *hex = PySwigObject_hex(v);    
01358   PyObject *repr = PyString_FromFormat("<Swig Object of type '%s' at 0x%s>", name, PyString_AsString(hex));
01359   Py_DECREF(hex);
01360   if (v->next) {
01361 #ifdef METH_NOARGS
01362     PyObject *nrep = PySwigObject_repr((PySwigObject *)v->next);
01363 #else
01364     PyObject *nrep = PySwigObject_repr((PySwigObject *)v->next, args);
01365 #endif
01366     PyString_ConcatAndDel(&repr,nrep);
01367   }
01368   return repr;  
01369 }
01370 
01371 SWIGRUNTIME int
01372 PySwigObject_print(PySwigObject *v, FILE *fp, int SWIGUNUSEDPARM(flags))
01373 {
01374 #ifdef METH_NOARGS
01375   PyObject *repr = PySwigObject_repr(v);
01376 #else
01377   PyObject *repr = PySwigObject_repr(v, NULL);
01378 #endif
01379   if (repr) {
01380     fputs(PyString_AsString(repr), fp);
01381     Py_DECREF(repr);
01382     return 0; 
01383   } else {
01384     return 1; 
01385   }
01386 }

01388 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01389 PySwigObject_str(PySwigObject *v)
01390 {
01391   char result[SWIG_BUFFER_SIZE];
01392   return SWIG_PackVoidPtr(result, v->ptr, v->ty->name, sizeof(result)) ?
01393     PyString_FromString(result) : 0;
01394 }

01396 SWIGRUNTIME int
01397 PySwigObject_compare(PySwigObject *v, PySwigObject *w)
01398 {
01399   void *i = v->ptr;
01400   void *j = w->ptr;
01401   return (i < j) ? -1 : ((i > j) ? 1 : 0);
01402 }

01412 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE int
01413 PySwigObject_Check(PyObject *op) {
01414   return ((op)->ob_type == PySwigObject_type())
01415     || (strcmp((op)->ob_type->tp_name,"PySwigObject") == 0);
01416 }
01417 
01418 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01419 PySwigObject_New(void *ptr, swig_type_info *ty, int own);
01420 
01421 SWIGRUNTIME void
01422 PySwigObject_dealloc(PyObject *v)
01423 {
01424   PySwigObject *sobj = (PySwigObject *) v;
01425   PyObject *next = sobj->next;
01426   if (sobj->own == SWIG_POINTER_OWN) {
01427     swig_type_info *ty = sobj->ty;
01428     PySwigClientData *data = ty ? (PySwigClientData *) ty->clientdata : 0;
01429     PyObject *destroy = data ? data->destroy : 0;
01430     if (destroy) {
01431       /* destroy is always a VARARGS method */
01432       PyObject *res;
01433       if (data->delargs) {
01434     /* we need to create a temporal object to carry the destroy operation */
01435     PyObject *tmp = PySwigObject_New(sobj->ptr, ty, 0);
01436     res = SWIG_Python_CallFunctor(destroy, tmp);
01437     Py_DECREF(tmp);
01438       } else {
01439     PyCFunction meth = PyCFunction_GET_FUNCTION(destroy);
01440     PyObject *mself = PyCFunction_GET_SELF(destroy);
01441     res = ((*meth)(mself, v));
01442       }
01443       Py_XDECREF(res);
01444     } 
01445 #if !defined(SWIG_PYTHON_SILENT_MEMLEAK)
01446     else {
01447       const char *name = SWIG_TypePrettyName(ty);
01448       printf("swig/python detected a memory leak of type '%s', no destructor found.\n", (name ? name : "unknown"));
01449     }
01450 #endif
01451   } 
01452   Py_XDECREF(next);
01453   PyObject_DEL(v);
01454 }
01455 
01456 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject* 
01457 PySwigObject_append(PyObject* v, PyObject* next)
01458 {
01459   PySwigObject *sobj = (PySwigObject *) v;
01460 #ifndef METH_O
01461   PyObject *tmp = 0;
01462   if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(next,(char *)"O:append", &tmp)) return NULL;
01463   next = tmp;
01464 #endif
01465   if (!PySwigObject_Check(next)) {
01466     return NULL;
01467   }
01468   sobj->next = next;
01469   Py_INCREF(next);
01470   return SWIG_Py_Void();
01471 }
01472 
01473 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject* 
01474 #ifdef METH_NOARGS
01475 PySwigObject_next(PyObject* v)
01476 #else
01477 PySwigObject_next(PyObject* v, PyObject *SWIGUNUSEDPARM(args))
01478 #endif
01479 {
01480   PySwigObject *sobj = (PySwigObject *) v;
01481   if (sobj->next) {    
01482     Py_INCREF(sobj->next);
01483     return sobj->next;
01484   } else {
01485     return SWIG_Py_Void();
01486   }
01487 }

01493 PySwigObject_disown(PyObject* v, PyObject *SWIGUNUSEDPARM(args))
01494 #endif

01501 SWIGINTERN PyObject*
01502 #ifdef METH_NOARGS
01503 PySwigObject_acquire(PyObject *v)
01504 #else
01505 PySwigObject_acquire(PyObject* v, PyObject *SWIGUNUSEDPARM(args))
01506 #endif
01507 {
01508   PySwigObject *sobj = (PySwigObject *)v;
01509   sobj->own = SWIG_POINTER_OWN;
01510   return SWIG_Py_Void();
01511 }
01512 
01513 SWIGINTERN PyObject*
01514 PySwigObject_own(PyObject *v, PyObject *args)
01515 {
01516   PyObject *val = 0;
01517 #if (PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x02020000)
01518   if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args,(char *)"|O:own",&val))
01519 #else
01520   if (!PyArg_UnpackTuple(args, (char *)"own", 0, 1, &val)) 
01521 #endif
01522     {
01523       return NULL;
01524     } 
01525   else
01526     {
01527       PySwigObject *sobj = (PySwigObject *)v;
01528       PyObject *obj = PyBool_FromLong(sobj->own);
01529       if (val) {
01530 #ifdef METH_NOARGS
01531     if (PyObject_IsTrue(val)) {
01532       PySwigObject_acquire(v);
01533     } else {
01534       PySwigObject_disown(v);
01535     }
01536 #else
01537     if (PyObject_IsTrue(val)) {
01538       PySwigObject_acquire(v,args);
01539     } else {
01540       PySwigObject_disown(v,args);
01541     }
01542 #endif
01543       } 
01544       return obj;
01545     }
01546 }

01552   {(char *)"acquire", (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_acquire, METH_NOARGS,  (char *)"aquires ownership of the pointer"},
01553   {(char *)"own",     (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_own,     METH_VARARGS, (char *)"returns/sets ownership of the pointer"},
01554   {(char *)"append",  (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_append,  METH_O,       (char *)"appends another 'this' object"},
01555   {(char *)"next",    (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_next,    METH_NOARGS,  (char *)"returns the next 'this' object"},
01556   {(char *)"__repr__",(PyCFunction)PySwigObject_repr,    METH_NOARGS,  (char *)"returns object representation"},
01557   {0, 0, 0, 0}  
01558 };
01559 #else
01560 static PyMethodDef
01561 swigobject_methods[] = {
01562   {(char *)"disown",  (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_disown,  METH_VARARGS,  (char *)"releases ownership of the pointer"},
01563   {(char *)"acquire", (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_acquire, METH_VARARGS,  (char *)"aquires ownership of the pointer"},
01564   {(char *)"own",     (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_own,     METH_VARARGS,  (char *)"returns/sets ownership of the pointer"},
01565   {(char *)"append",  (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_append,  METH_VARARGS,  (char *)"appends another 'this' object"},
01566   {(char *)"next",    (PyCFunction)PySwigObject_next,    METH_VARARGS,  (char *)"returns the next 'this' object"},
01567   {(char *)"__repr__",(PyCFunction)PySwigObject_repr,   METH_VARARGS,  (char *)"returns object representation"},
01568   {0, 0, 0, 0}  
01569 };
01570 #endif

01701 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
01702  * Implements a simple Swig Packed type, and use it instead of string
01703  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
01704 
01705 typedef struct {
01706   PyObject_HEAD
01707   void *pack;
01708   swig_type_info *ty;
01709   size_t size;
01710 } PySwigPacked;
01711 
01712 SWIGRUNTIME int
01713 PySwigPacked_print(PySwigPacked *v, FILE *fp, int SWIGUNUSEDPARM(flags))
01714 {
01715   char result[SWIG_BUFFER_SIZE];
01716   fputs("<Swig Packed ", fp); 
01717   if (SWIG_PackDataName(result, v->pack, v->size, 0, sizeof(result))) {
01718     fputs("at ", fp); 
01719     fputs(result, fp); 
01720   }
01721   fputs(v->ty->name,fp); 
01722   fputs(">", fp);
01723   return 0; 
01724 }
01725   
01726 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01727 PySwigPacked_repr(PySwigPacked *v)
01728 {
01729   char result[SWIG_BUFFER_SIZE];
01730   if (SWIG_PackDataName(result, v->pack, v->size, 0, sizeof(result))) {
01731     return PyString_FromFormat("<Swig Packed at %s%s>", result, v->ty->name);
01732   } else {
01733     return PyString_FromFormat("<Swig Packed %s>", v->ty->name);
01734   }  
01735 }
01736 
01737 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01738 PySwigPacked_str(PySwigPacked *v)
01739 {
01740   char result[SWIG_BUFFER_SIZE];
01741   if (SWIG_PackDataName(result, v->pack, v->size, 0, sizeof(result))){
01742     return PyString_FromFormat("%s%s", result, v->ty->name);
01743   } else {
01744     return PyString_FromString(v->ty->name);
01745   }  
01746 }
01747 
01748 SWIGRUNTIME int
01749 PySwigPacked_compare(PySwigPacked *v, PySwigPacked *w)
01750 {
01751   size_t i = v->size;
01752   size_t j = w->size;
01753   int s = (i < j) ? -1 : ((i > j) ? 1 : 0);
01754   return s ? s : strncmp((char *)v->pack, (char *)w->pack, 2*v->size);
01755 }

01808     0,                          /* tp_as_buffer */
01809     Py_TPFLAGS_DEFAULT,             /* tp_flags */
01810     swigpacked_doc,                 /* tp_doc */
01811     0,                                  /* tp_traverse */
01812     0,                                  /* tp_clear */
01813     0,                                  /* tp_richcompare */
01814     0,                                  /* tp_weaklistoffset */
01815 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02020000
01816     0,                                  /* tp_iter */
01817     0,                                  /* tp_iternext */
01818     0,                          /* tp_methods */ 
01819     0,                      /* tp_members */
01820     0,                  /* tp_getset */         
01821     0,                      /* tp_base */           
01822     0,                  /* tp_dict */           
01823     0,                  /* tp_descr_get */      
01824     0,                  /* tp_descr_set */      
01825     0,                  /* tp_dictoffset */     
01826     0,                  /* tp_init */           
01827     0,                  /* tp_alloc */          
01828     0,                      /* tp_new */            
01829     0,                              /* tp_free */      
01830         0,                                  /* tp_is_gc */  
01831     0,                  /* tp_bases */   
01832     0,                  /* tp_mro */
01833     0,                  /* tp_cache */   
01834     0,                  /* tp_subclasses */
01835     0,                  /* tp_weaklist */
01836 #endif
01837 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02030000
01838     0,                                  /* tp_del */
01839 #endif
01840 #ifdef COUNT_ALLOCS
01841     0,0,0,0                             /* tp_alloc -> tp_next */
01842 #endif
01843       };
01844     pyswigpacked_type = tmp;
01845     pyswigpacked_type.ob_type = &PyType_Type;
01846     type_init = 1;
01847   }
01848   return &pyswigpacked_type;
01849 }
01850 
01851 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01852 PySwigPacked_New(void *ptr, size_t size, swig_type_info *ty)
01853 {
01854   PySwigPacked *sobj = PyObject_NEW(PySwigPacked, PySwigPacked_type());
01855   if (sobj) {
01856     void *pack = malloc(size);
01857     if (pack) {
01858       memcpy(pack, ptr, size);
01859       sobj->pack = pack;
01860       sobj->ty   = ty;
01861       sobj->size = size;
01862     } else {
01863       PyObject_DEL((PyObject *) sobj);
01864       sobj = 0;
01865     }
01866   }
01867   return (PyObject *) sobj;
01868 }
01869 
01870 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
01871 PySwigPacked_UnpackData(PyObject *obj, void *ptr, size_t size)
01872 {
01873   if (PySwigPacked_Check(obj)) {
01874     PySwigPacked *sobj = (PySwigPacked *)obj;
01875     if (sobj->size != size) return 0;
01876     memcpy(ptr, sobj->pack, size);
01877     return sobj->ty;
01878   } else {
01879     return 0;
01880   }
01881 }

01883 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
01884  * pointers/data manipulation
01885  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
01886 
01887 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE PyObject *
01888 _SWIG_This(void)
01889 {
01890   return PyString_FromString("this");
01891 }
01892 
01893 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
01894 SWIG_This(void)
01895 {
01896   static PyObject *SWIG_STATIC_POINTER(swig_this) = _SWIG_This();
01897   return swig_this;
01898 }
01899 
01900 /* #define SWIG_PYTHON_SLOW_GETSET_THIS */
01901 
01902 SWIGRUNTIME PySwigObject *
01903 SWIG_Python_GetSwigThis(PyObject *pyobj) 
01904 {
01905   if (PySwigObject_Check(pyobj)) {
01906     return (PySwigObject *) pyobj;
01907   } else {
01908     PyObject *obj = 0;
01909 #if (!defined(SWIG_PYTHON_SLOW_GETSET_THIS) && (PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02030000))
01910     if (PyInstance_Check(pyobj)) {
01911       obj = _PyInstance_Lookup(pyobj, SWIG_This());      
01912     } else {
01913       PyObject **dictptr = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(pyobj);
01914       if (dictptr != NULL) {
01915     PyObject *dict = *dictptr;
01916     obj = dict ? PyDict_GetItem(dict, SWIG_This()) : 0;
01917       } else {
01918 #ifdef PyWeakref_CheckProxy
01919     if (PyWeakref_CheckProxy(pyobj)) {
01920       PyObject *wobj = PyWeakref_GET_OBJECT(pyobj);
01921       return wobj ? SWIG_Python_GetSwigThis(wobj) : 0;
01922     }
01923 #endif
01924     obj = PyObject_GetAttr(pyobj,SWIG_This());
01925     if (obj) {
01926       Py_DECREF(obj);
01927     } else {
01928       if (PyErr_Occurred()) PyErr_Clear();
01929       return 0;
01930     }
01931       }
01932     }
01933 #else
01934     obj = PyObject_GetAttr(pyobj,SWIG_This());
01935     if (obj) {
01936       Py_DECREF(obj);
01937     } else {
01938       if (PyErr_Occurred()) PyErr_Clear();
01939       return 0;
01940     }
01941 #endif
01942     if (obj && !PySwigObject_Check(obj)) {
01943       /* a PyObject is called 'this', try to get the 'real this'
01944      PySwigObject from it */ 
01945       return SWIG_Python_GetSwigThis(obj);
01946     }
01947     return (PySwigObject *)obj;
01948   }
01949 }
01950 
01951 /* Acquire a pointer value */
01952 
01953 SWIGRUNTIME int
01954 SWIG_Python_AcquirePtr(PyObject *obj, int own) {
01955   if (own == SWIG_POINTER_OWN) {
01956     PySwigObject *sobj = SWIG_Python_GetSwigThis(obj);
01957     if (sobj) {
01958       int oldown = sobj->own;
01959       sobj->own = own;
01960       return oldown;
01961     }
01962   }
01963   return 0;
01964 }
01965 
01966 /* Convert a pointer value */
01967 
01968 SWIGRUNTIME int
01969 SWIG_Python_ConvertPtrAndOwn(PyObject *obj, void **ptr, swig_type_info *ty, int flags, int *own) {
01970   if (!obj) return SWIG_ERROR;
01971   if (obj == Py_None) {
01972     if (ptr) *ptr = 0;
01973     return SWIG_OK;
01974   } else {
01975     PySwigObject *sobj = SWIG_Python_GetSwigThis(obj);
01976     if (own)
01977       *own = 0;
01978     while (sobj) {
01979       void *vptr = sobj->ptr;
01980       if (ty) {
01981     swig_type_info *to = sobj->ty;
01982     if (to == ty) {
01983       /* no type cast needed */
01984       if (ptr) *ptr = vptr;
01985       break;
01986     } else {
01987       swig_cast_info *tc = SWIG_TypeCheck(to->name,ty);
01988       if (!tc) {
01989         sobj = (PySwigObject *)sobj->next;
01990       } else {
01991         if (ptr) {
01992               int newmemory = 0;
01993               *ptr = SWIG_TypeCast(tc,vptr,&newmemory);
01994               if (newmemory == SWIG_CAST_NEW_MEMORY) {
01995                 assert(own);
01996                 if (own)
01997                   *own = *own | SWIG_CAST_NEW_MEMORY;
01998               }
01999             }
02000         break;
02001       }
02002     }
02003       } else {
02004     if (ptr) *ptr = vptr;
02005     break;
02006       }
02007     }
02008     if (sobj) {
02009       if (own)
02010         *own = *own | sobj->own;
02011       if (flags & SWIG_POINTER_DISOWN) {
02012     sobj->own = 0;
02013       }
02014       return SWIG_OK;
02015     } else {
02016       int res = SWIG_ERROR;
02017       if (flags & SWIG_POINTER_IMPLICIT_CONV) {
02018     PySwigClientData *data = ty ? (PySwigClientData *) ty->clientdata : 0;
02019     if (data && !data->implicitconv) {
02020       PyObject *klass = data->klass;
02021       if (klass) {
02022         PyObject *impconv;
02023         data->implicitconv = 1; /* avoid recursion and call 'explicit' constructors*/
02024         impconv = SWIG_Python_CallFunctor(klass, obj);
02025         data->implicitconv = 0;
02026         if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
02027           PyErr_Clear();
02028           impconv = 0;
02029         }
02030         if (impconv) {
02031           PySwigObject *iobj = SWIG_Python_GetSwigThis(impconv);
02032           if (iobj) {
02033         void *vptr;
02034         res = SWIG_Python_ConvertPtrAndOwn((PyObject*)iobj, &vptr, ty, 0, 0);
02035         if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
02036           if (ptr) {
02037             *ptr = vptr;
02038             /* transfer the ownership to 'ptr' */
02039             iobj->own = 0;
02040             res = SWIG_AddCast(res);
02041             res = SWIG_AddNewMask(res);
02042           } else {
02043             res = SWIG_AddCast(res);            
02044           }
02045         }
02046           }
02047           Py_DECREF(impconv);
02048         }
02049       }
02050     }
02051       }
02052       return res;
02053     }
02054   }
02055 }
02056 
02057 /* Convert a function ptr value */
02058 
02059 SWIGRUNTIME int
02060 SWIG_Python_ConvertFunctionPtr(PyObject *obj, void **ptr, swig_type_info *ty) {
02061   if (!PyCFunction_Check(obj)) {
02062     return SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj, ptr, ty, 0);
02063   } else {
02064     void *vptr = 0;
02065     
02066     /* here we get the method pointer for callbacks */
02067     const char *doc = (((PyCFunctionObject *)obj) -> m_ml -> ml_doc);
02068     const char *desc = doc ? strstr(doc, "swig_ptr: ") : 0;
02069     if (desc) {
02070       desc = ty ? SWIG_UnpackVoidPtr(desc + 10, &vptr, ty->name) : 0;
02071       if (!desc) return SWIG_ERROR;
02072     }
02073     if (ty) {
02074       swig_cast_info *tc = SWIG_TypeCheck(desc,ty);
02075       if (tc) {
02076         int newmemory = 0;
02077         *ptr = SWIG_TypeCast(tc,vptr,&newmemory);
02078         assert(!newmemory); /* newmemory handling not yet implemented */
02079       } else {
02080         return SWIG_ERROR;
02081       }
02082     } else {
02083       *ptr = vptr;
02084     }
02085     return SWIG_OK;
02086   }
02087 }
02088 
02089 /* Convert a packed value value */
02090 
02091 SWIGRUNTIME int
02092 SWIG_Python_ConvertPacked(PyObject *obj, void *ptr, size_t sz, swig_type_info *ty) {
02093   swig_type_info *to = PySwigPacked_UnpackData(obj, ptr, sz);
02094   if (!to) return SWIG_ERROR;
02095   if (ty) {
02096     if (to != ty) {
02097       /* check type cast? */
02098       swig_cast_info *tc = SWIG_TypeCheck(to->name,ty);
02099       if (!tc) return SWIG_ERROR;
02100     }
02101   }
02102   return SWIG_OK;
02103 }

02105 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
02106  * Create a new pointer object
02107  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
02108 
02109 /*
02110   Create a new instance object, whitout calling __init__, and set the
02111   'this' attribute.
02112 */
02113 
02114 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject* 
02115 SWIG_Python_NewShadowInstance(PySwigClientData *data, PyObject *swig_this)
02116 {
02117 #if (PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02020000)
02118   PyObject *inst = 0;
02119   PyObject *newraw = data->newraw;
02120   if (newraw) {
02121     inst = PyObject_Call(newraw, data->newargs, NULL);
02122     if (inst) {
02123 #if !defined(SWIG_PYTHON_SLOW_GETSET_THIS)
02124       PyObject **dictptr = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(inst);
02125       if (dictptr != NULL) {
02126     PyObject *dict = *dictptr;
02127     if (dict == NULL) {
02128       dict = PyDict_New();
02129       *dictptr = dict;
02130       PyDict_SetItem(dict, SWIG_This(), swig_this);
02131     }
02132       }
02133 #else
02134       PyObject *key = SWIG_This();
02135       PyObject_SetAttr(inst, key, swig_this);
02136 #endif
02137     }
02138   } else {
02139     PyObject *dict = PyDict_New();
02140     PyDict_SetItem(dict, SWIG_This(), swig_this);
02141     inst = PyInstance_NewRaw(data->newargs, dict);
02142     Py_DECREF(dict);
02143   }
02144   return inst;
02145 #else
02146 #if (PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02010000)
02147   PyObject *inst;
02148   PyObject *dict = PyDict_New();
02149   PyDict_SetItem(dict, SWIG_This(), swig_this);
02150   inst = PyInstance_NewRaw(data->newargs, dict);
02151   Py_DECREF(dict);
02152   return (PyObject *) inst;
02153 #else
02154   PyInstanceObject *inst = PyObject_NEW(PyInstanceObject, &PyInstance_Type);
02155   if (inst == NULL) {
02156     return NULL;
02157   }
02158   inst->in_class = (PyClassObject *)data->newargs;
02159   Py_INCREF(inst->in_class);
02160   inst->in_dict = PyDict_New();
02161   if (inst->in_dict == NULL) {
02162     Py_DECREF(inst);
02163     return NULL;
02164   }
02165 #ifdef Py_TPFLAGS_HAVE_WEAKREFS
02166   inst->in_weakreflist = NULL;
02167 #endif
02168 #ifdef Py_TPFLAGS_GC
02169   PyObject_GC_Init(inst);
02170 #endif
02171   PyDict_SetItem(inst->in_dict, SWIG_This(), swig_this);
02172   return (PyObject *) inst;
02173 #endif
02174 #endif
02175 }
02176 
02177 SWIGRUNTIME void
02178 SWIG_Python_SetSwigThis(PyObject *inst, PyObject *swig_this)
02179 {
02180  PyObject *dict;
02181 #if (PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02020000) && !defined(SWIG_PYTHON_SLOW_GETSET_THIS)
02182  PyObject **dictptr = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(inst);
02183  if (dictptr != NULL) {
02184    dict = *dictptr;
02185    if (dict == NULL) {
02186      dict = PyDict_New();
02187      *dictptr = dict;
02188    }
02189    PyDict_SetItem(dict, SWIG_This(), swig_this);
02190    return;
02191  }
02192 #endif
02193  dict = PyObject_GetAttrString(inst, (char*)"__dict__");
02194  PyDict_SetItem(dict, SWIG_This(), swig_this);
02195  Py_DECREF(dict);
02196 } 
02197 
02198 
02199 SWIGINTERN PyObject *
02200 SWIG_Python_InitShadowInstance(PyObject *args) {
02201   PyObject *obj[2];
02202   if (!SWIG_Python_UnpackTuple(args,(char*)"swiginit", 2, 2, obj)) {
02203     return NULL;
02204   } else {
02205     PySwigObject *sthis = SWIG_Python_GetSwigThis(obj[0]);
02206     if (sthis) {
02207       PySwigObject_append((PyObject*) sthis, obj[1]);
02208     } else {
02209       SWIG_Python_SetSwigThis(obj[0], obj[1]);
02210     }
02211     return SWIG_Py_Void();
02212   }
02213 }
02214 
02215 /* Create a new pointer object */
02216 
02217 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
02218 SWIG_Python_NewPointerObj(void *ptr, swig_type_info *type, int flags) {
02219   if (!ptr) {
02220     return SWIG_Py_Void();
02221   } else {
02222     int own = (flags & SWIG_POINTER_OWN) ? SWIG_POINTER_OWN : 0;
02223     PyObject *robj = PySwigObject_New(ptr, type, own);
02224     PySwigClientData *clientdata = type ? (PySwigClientData *)(type->clientdata) : 0;
02225     if (clientdata && !(flags & SWIG_POINTER_NOSHADOW)) {
02226       PyObject *inst = SWIG_Python_NewShadowInstance(clientdata, robj);
02227       if (inst) {
02228     Py_DECREF(robj);
02229     robj = inst;
02230       }
02231     }
02232     return robj;
02233   }
02234 }

02238 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE PyObject *
02239 SWIG_Python_NewPackedObj(void *ptr, size_t sz, swig_type_info *type) {
02240   return ptr ? PySwigPacked_New((void *) ptr, sz, type) : SWIG_Py_Void();
02241 }

02244  *  Get type list 
02245  * -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
02246 
02247 #ifdef SWIG_LINK_RUNTIME
02248 void *SWIG_ReturnGlobalTypeList(void *);
02249 #endif
02250 
02251 SWIGRUNTIME swig_module_info *
02252 SWIG_Python_GetModule(void) {
02253   static void *type_pointer = (void *)0;
02254   /* first check if module already created */
02255   if (!type_pointer) {
02256 #ifdef SWIG_LINK_RUNTIME
02257     type_pointer = SWIG_ReturnGlobalTypeList((void *)0);
02258 #else
02259     type_pointer = PyCObject_Import((char*)"swig_runtime_data" SWIG_RUNTIME_VERSION,
02260                     (char*)"type_pointer" SWIG_TYPE_TABLE_NAME);
02261     if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
02262       PyErr_Clear();
02263       type_pointer = (void *)0;
02264     }
02265 #endif
02266   }
02267   return (swig_module_info *) type_pointer;
02268 }
02269 
02270 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 2
02271 /* PyModule_AddObject function was introduced in Python 2.0.  The following function
02272    is copied out of Python/modsupport.c in python version 2.3.4 */
02273 SWIGINTERN int
02274 PyModule_AddObject(PyObject *m, char *name, PyObject *o)
02275 {
02276   PyObject *dict;
02277   if (!PyModule_Check(m)) {
02278     PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
02279             "PyModule_AddObject() needs module as first arg");
02280     return SWIG_ERROR;
02281   }
02282   if (!o) {
02283     PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
02284             "PyModule_AddObject() needs non-NULL value");
02285     return SWIG_ERROR;
02286   }
02287   
02288   dict = PyModule_GetDict(m);
02289   if (dict == NULL) {
02290     /* Internal error -- modules must have a dict! */
02291     PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError, "module '%s' has no __dict__",
02292          PyModule_GetName(m));
02293     return SWIG_ERROR;
02294   }
02295   if (PyDict_SetItemString(dict, name, o))
02296     return SWIG_ERROR;
02297   Py_DECREF(o);
02298   return SWIG_OK;
02299 }
02300 #endif
02301 
02302 SWIGRUNTIME void
02303 SWIG_Python_DestroyModule(void *vptr)
02304 {
02305   swig_module_info *swig_module = (swig_module_info *) vptr;
02306   swig_type_info **types = swig_module->types;
02307   size_t i;
02308   for (i =0; i < swig_module->size; ++i) {
02309     swig_type_info *ty = types[i];
02310     if (ty->owndata) {
02311       PySwigClientData *data = (PySwigClientData *) ty->clientdata;
02312       if (data) PySwigClientData_Del(data);
02313     }
02314   }
02315   Py_DECREF(SWIG_This());
02316 }
02317 
02318 SWIGRUNTIME void
02319 SWIG_Python_SetModule(swig_module_info *swig_module) {
02320   static PyMethodDef swig_empty_runtime_method_table[] = { {NULL, NULL, 0, NULL} };/* Sentinel */
02321 
02322   PyObject *module = Py_InitModule((char*)"swig_runtime_data" SWIG_RUNTIME_VERSION,
02323                    swig_empty_runtime_method_table);
02324   PyObject *pointer = PyCObject_FromVoidPtr((void *) swig_module, SWIG_Python_DestroyModule);
02325   if (pointer && module) {
02326     PyModule_AddObject(module, (char*)"type_pointer" SWIG_TYPE_TABLE_NAME, pointer);
02327   } else {
02328     Py_XDECREF(pointer);
02329   }
02330 }
02331 
02332 /* The python cached type query */
02333 SWIGRUNTIME PyObject *
02334 SWIG_Python_TypeCache(void) {
02335   static PyObject *SWIG_STATIC_POINTER(cache) = PyDict_New();
02336   return cache;
02337 }
02338 
02339 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
02340 SWIG_Python_TypeQuery(const char *type)
02341 {
02342   PyObject *cache = SWIG_Python_TypeCache();
02343   PyObject *key = PyString_FromString(type); 
02344   PyObject *obj = PyDict_GetItem(cache, key);
02345   swig_type_info *descriptor;
02346   if (obj) {
02347     descriptor = (swig_type_info *) PyCObject_AsVoidPtr(obj);
02348   } else {
02349     swig_module_info *swig_module = SWIG_Python_GetModule();
02350     descriptor = SWIG_TypeQueryModule(swig_module, swig_module, type);
02351     if (descriptor) {
02352       obj = PyCObject_FromVoidPtr(descriptor, NULL);
02353       PyDict_SetItem(cache, key, obj);
02354       Py_DECREF(obj);
02355     }
02356   }
02357   Py_DECREF(key);
02358   return descriptor;
02359 }

02361 /* 
02362    For backward compatibility only
02363 */
02364 #define SWIG_POINTER_EXCEPTION  0
02365 #define SWIG_arg_fail(arg)      SWIG_Python_ArgFail(arg)
02366 #define SWIG_MustGetPtr(p, type, argnum, flags)  SWIG_Python_MustGetPtr(p, type, argnum, flags)
02367 
02368 SWIGRUNTIME int
02369 SWIG_Python_AddErrMesg(const char* mesg, int infront)
02370 {
02371   if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
02372     PyObject *type = 0;
02373     PyObject *value = 0;
02374     PyObject *traceback = 0;
02375     PyErr_Fetch(&type, &value, &traceback);
02376     if (value) {
02377       PyObject *old_str = PyObject_Str(value);
02378       Py_XINCREF(type);
02379       PyErr_Clear();
02380       if (infront) {
02381     PyErr_Format(type, "%s %s", mesg, PyString_AsString(old_str));
02382       } else {
02383     PyErr_Format(type, "%s %s", PyString_AsString(old_str), mesg);
02384       }
02385       Py_DECREF(old_str);
02386     }
02387     return 1;
02388   } else {
02389     return 0;
02390   }
02391 }
02392   
02393 SWIGRUNTIME int
02394 SWIG_Python_ArgFail(int argnum)
02395 {
02396   if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
02397     /* add information about failing argument */
02398     char mesg[256];
02399     PyOS_snprintf(mesg, sizeof(mesg), "argument number %d:", argnum);
02400     return SWIG_Python_AddErrMesg(mesg, 1);
02401   } else {
02402     return 0;
02403   }
02404 }

02406 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE const char *
02407 PySwigObject_GetDesc(PyObject *self)
02408 {
02409   PySwigObject *v = (PySwigObject *)self;
02410   swig_type_info *ty = v ? v->ty : 0;
02411   return ty ? ty->str : (char*)"";
02412 }
02413 
02414 SWIGRUNTIME void
02415 SWIG_Python_TypeError(const char *type, PyObject *obj)
02416 {
02417   if (type) {
02418 #if defined(SWIG_COBJECT_TYPES)
02419     if (obj && PySwigObject_Check(obj)) {
02420       const char *otype = (const char *) PySwigObject_GetDesc(obj);
02421       if (otype) {
02422     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "a '%s' is expected, 'PySwigObject(%s)' is received",
02423              type, otype);
02424     return;
02425       }
02426     } else 
02427 #endif      
02428     {
02429       const char *otype = (obj ? obj->ob_type->tp_name : 0); 
02430       if (otype) {
02431     PyObject *str = PyObject_Str(obj);
02432     const char *cstr = str ? PyString_AsString(str) : 0;
02433     if (cstr) {
02434       PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "a '%s' is expected, '%s(%s)' is received",
02435                type, otype, cstr);
02436     } else {
02437       PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "a '%s' is expected, '%s' is received",
02438                type, otype);
02439     }
02440     Py_XDECREF(str);
02441     return;
02442       }
02443     }   
02444     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "a '%s' is expected", type);
02445   } else {
02446     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "unexpected type is received");
02447   }
02448 }

02453 SWIG_Python_MustGetPtr(PyObject *obj, swig_type_info *ty, int argnum, int flags) {
02454   void *result;

02456     PyErr_Clear();
02457     if (flags & SWIG_POINTER_EXCEPTION) {
02458       SWIG_Python_TypeError(SWIG_TypePrettyName(ty), obj);
02459       SWIG_Python_ArgFail(argnum);
02460     }
02461   }
02462   return result;
02463 }

02563 SWIGINTERN int
02564 SWIG_AsVal_double (PyObject *obj, double *val)
02565 {
02566   int res = SWIG_TypeError;
02567   if (PyFloat_Check(obj)) {
02568     if (val) *val = PyFloat_AsDouble(obj);
02569     return SWIG_OK;
02570   } else if (PyInt_Check(obj)) {
02571     if (val) *val = PyInt_AsLong(obj);
02572     return SWIG_OK;
02573   } else if (PyLong_Check(obj)) {
02574     double v = PyLong_AsDouble(obj);
02575     if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
02576       if (val) *val = v;
02577       return SWIG_OK;
02578     } else {
02579       PyErr_Clear();
02580     }
02581   }
02582 #ifdef SWIG_PYTHON_CAST_MODE
02583   {
02584     int dispatch = 0;
02585     double d = PyFloat_AsDouble(obj);
02586     if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
02587       if (val) *val = d;
02588       return SWIG_AddCast(SWIG_OK);
02589     } else {
02590       PyErr_Clear();
02591     }
02592     if (!dispatch) {
02593       long v = PyLong_AsLong(obj);
02594       if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
02595     if (val) *val = v;
02596     return SWIG_AddCast(SWIG_AddCast(SWIG_OK));
02597       } else {
02598     PyErr_Clear();
02599       }
02600     }
02601   }
02602 #endif
02603   return res;
02604 }

02612 
02613 SWIGINTERNINLINE int
02614 SWIG_CanCastAsInteger(double *d, double min, double max) {
02615   double x = *d;
02616   if ((min <= x && x <= max)) {
02617    double fx = floor(x);
02618    double cx = ceil(x);
02619    double rd =  ((x - fx) < 0.5) ? fx : cx; /* simple rint */
02620    if ((errno == EDOM) || (errno == ERANGE)) {
02621      errno = 0;
02622    } else {
02623      double summ, reps, diff;
02624      if (rd < x) {
02625        diff = x - rd;
02626      } else if (rd > x) {
02627        diff = rd - x;
02628      } else {
02629        return 1;
02630      }
02631      summ = rd + x;
02632      reps = diff/summ;
02633      if (reps < 8*DBL_EPSILON) {
02634        *d = rd;
02635        return 1;
02636      }
02637    }
02638   }
02639   return 0;
02640 }

02643 SWIGINTERN int
02644 SWIG_AsVal_long (PyObject *obj, long* val)
02645 {
02646   if (PyInt_Check(obj)) {
02647     if (val) *val = PyInt_AsLong(obj);
02648     return SWIG_OK;
02649   } else if (PyLong_Check(obj)) {
02650     long v = PyLong_AsLong(obj);
02651     if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
02652       if (val) *val = v;
02653       return SWIG_OK;
02654     } else {
02655       PyErr_Clear();
02656     }
02657   }
02658 #ifdef SWIG_PYTHON_CAST_MODE
02659   {
02660     int dispatch = 0;
02661     long v = PyInt_AsLong(obj);
02662     if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
02663       if (val) *val = v;
02664       return SWIG_AddCast(SWIG_OK);
02665     } else {
02666       PyErr_Clear();
02667     }
02668     if (!dispatch) {
02669       double d;
02670       int res = SWIG_AddCast(SWIG_AsVal_double (obj,&d));
02671       if (SWIG_IsOK(res) && SWIG_CanCastAsInteger(&d, LONG_MIN, LONG_MAX)) {
02672     if (val) *val = (long)(d);
02673     return res;
02674       }
02675     }
02676   }
02677 #endif
02678   return SWIG_TypeError;
02679 }

02683 SWIG_AsVal_int (PyObject * obj, int *val)
02684 {
02685   long v;
02686   int res = SWIG_AsVal_long (obj, &v);
02687   if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
02688     if ((v < INT_MIN || v > INT_MAX)) {
02689       return SWIG_OverflowError;
02690     } else {
02691       if (val) *val = (int)(v);
02692     }
02693   }  
02694   return res;

02733 SWIG_pchar_descriptor(void)

02736   static swig_type_info* info = 0;

02744 
02745 SWIGINTERN int
02746 SWIG_AsCharPtrAndSize(PyObject *obj, char** cptr, size_t* psize, int *alloc)
02747 {
02748   if (PyString_Check(obj)) {
02749     char *cstr; Py_ssize_t len;
02750     PyString_AsStringAndSize(obj, &cstr, &len);
02751     if (cptr)  {
02752       if (alloc) {
02753     /* 
02754        In python the user should not be able to modify the inner
02755        string representation. To warranty that, if you define
02756        SWIG_PYTHON_SAFE_CSTRINGS, a new/copy of the python string
02757        buffer is always returned.
02758 
02759        The default behavior is just to return the pointer value,
02760        so, be careful.
02761     */ 
02762 #if defined(SWIG_PYTHON_SAFE_CSTRINGS)
02763     if (*alloc != SWIG_OLDOBJ) 
02764 #else
02765     if (*alloc == SWIG_NEWOBJ) 
02766 #endif
02767       {
02768         *cptr = (char *)memcpy((char *)malloc((len + 1)*sizeof(char)), cstr, sizeof(char)*(len + 1));
02769         *alloc = SWIG_NEWOBJ;
02770       }
02771     else {
02772       *cptr = cstr;
02773       *alloc = SWIG_OLDOBJ;
02774     }
02775       } else {
02776     *cptr = PyString_AsString(obj);
02777       }
02778     }
02779     if (psize) *psize = len + 1;
02780     return SWIG_OK;
02781   } else {
02782     swig_type_info* pchar_descriptor = SWIG_pchar_descriptor();
02783     if (pchar_descriptor) {
02784       void* vptr = 0;
02785       if (SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj, &vptr, pchar_descriptor, 0) == SWIG_OK) {
02786     if (cptr) *cptr = (char *) vptr;
02787     if (psize) *psize = vptr ? (strlen((char *)vptr) + 1) : 0;
02788     if (alloc) *alloc = SWIG_OLDOBJ;
02789     return SWIG_OK;
02790       }
02791     }
02792   }
02793   return SWIG_TypeError;
02794 }

02796 
02797 SWIGINTERN int
02798 SWIG_AsCharArray(PyObject * obj, char *val, size_t size)
02799 { 
02800   char* cptr = 0; size_t csize = 0; int alloc = SWIG_OLDOBJ;
02801   int res = SWIG_AsCharPtrAndSize(obj, &cptr, &csize, &alloc);
02802   if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
02803     if ((csize == size + 1) && cptr && !(cptr[csize-1])) --csize;
02804     if (csize <= size) {
02805       if (val) {
02806     if (csize) memcpy(val, cptr, csize*sizeof(char));
02807     if (csize < size) memset(val + csize, 0, (size - csize)*sizeof(char));
02808       }
02809       if (alloc == SWIG_NEWOBJ) {
02810     free((char*)cptr);
02811     res = SWIG_DelNewMask(res);
02812       }      
02813       return res;
02814     }
02815     if (alloc == SWIG_NEWOBJ) free((char*)cptr);
02816   }
02817   return SWIG_TypeError;
02818 }

02821 SWIGINTERNINLINE PyObject *
02822 SWIG_FromCharPtrAndSize(const char* carray, size_t size)
02823 {
02824   if (carray) {
02825     if (size > INT_MAX) {
02826       swig_type_info* pchar_descriptor = SWIG_pchar_descriptor();
02827       return pchar_descriptor ? 
02828     SWIG_NewPointerObj((char *)(carray), pchar_descriptor, 0) : SWIG_Py_Void();
02829     } else {
02830       return PyString_FromStringAndSize(carray, (int)(size));
02831     }
02832   } else {
02833     return SWIG_Py_Void();
02834   }
02835 }

12610 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12611  * Type initialization:
12612  * This problem is tough by the requirement that no dynamic 
12613  * memory is used. Also, since swig_type_info structures store pointers to 
12614  * swig_cast_info structures and swig_cast_info structures store pointers back
12615  * to swig_type_info structures, we need some lookup code at initialization. 
12616  * The idea is that swig generates all the structures that are needed. 
12617  * The runtime then collects these partially filled structures. 
12618  * The SWIG_InitializeModule function takes these initial arrays out of 
12619  * swig_module, and does all the lookup, filling in the swig_module.types
12620  * array with the correct data and linking the correct swig_cast_info
12621  * structures together.
12622  *
12623  * The generated swig_type_info structures are assigned staticly to an initial 
12624  * array. We just loop through that array, and handle each type individually.
12625  * First we lookup if this type has been already loaded, and if so, use the
12626  * loaded structure instead of the generated one. Then we have to fill in the
12627  * cast linked list. The cast data is initially stored in something like a
12628  * two-dimensional array. Each row corresponds to a type (there are the same
12629  * number of rows as there are in the swig_type_initial array). Each entry in
12630  * a column is one of the swig_cast_info structures for that type.
12631  * The cast_initial array is actually an array of arrays, because each row has
12632  * a variable number of columns. So to actually build the cast linked list,
12633  * we find the array of casts associated with the type, and loop through it 
12634  * adding the casts to the list. The one last trick we need to do is making
12635  * sure the type pointer in the swig_cast_info struct is correct.
12636  *
12637  * First off, we lookup the cast->type name to see if it is already loaded. 
12638  * There are three cases to handle:
12639  *  1) If the cast->type has already been loaded AND the type we are adding
12640  *     casting info to has not been loaded (it is in this module), THEN we
12641  *     replace the cast->type pointer with the type pointer that has already
12642  *     been loaded.
12643  *  2) If BOTH types (the one we are adding casting info to, and the 
12644  *     cast->type) are loaded, THEN the cast info has already been loaded by
12645  *     the previous module so we just ignore it.
12646  *  3) Finally, if cast->type has not already been loaded, then we add that
12647  *     swig_cast_info to the linked list (because the cast->type) pointer will
12648  *     be correct.
12649  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
12650 
12651 #ifdef __cplusplus
12652 extern "C" {
12653 #if 0
12654 } /* c-mode */
12655 #endif
12656 #endif
12657 
12658 #if 0
12659 #define SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12660 #endif

12662 
12663 SWIGRUNTIME void
12664 SWIG_InitializeModule(void *clientdata) {
12665   size_t i;
12666   swig_module_info *module_head, *iter;
12667   int found, init;
12668   
12669   clientdata = clientdata;
12670   
12671   /* check to see if the circular list has been setup, if not, set it up */
12672   if (swig_module.next==0) {
12673     /* Initialize the swig_module */
12674     swig_module.type_initial = swig_type_initial;
12675     swig_module.cast_initial = swig_cast_initial;
12676     swig_module.next = &swig_module;
12677     init = 1;
12678   } else {
12679     init = 0;
12680   }
12681   
12682   /* Try and load any already created modules */
12683   module_head = SWIG_GetModule(clientdata);
12684   if (!module_head) {
12685     /* This is the first module loaded for this interpreter */
12686     /* so set the swig module into the interpreter */
12687     SWIG_SetModule(clientdata, &swig_module);
12688     module_head = &swig_module;
12689   } else {
12690     /* the interpreter has loaded a SWIG module, but has it loaded this one? */
12691     found=0;
12692     iter=module_head;
12693     do {
12694       if (iter==&swig_module) {
12695         found=1;
12696         break;
12697       }
12698       iter=iter->next;
12699     } while (iter!= module_head);
12700     
12701     /* if the is found in the list, then all is done and we may leave */
12702     if (found) return;
12703     /* otherwise we must add out module into the list */
12704     swig_module.next = module_head->next;
12705     module_head->next = &swig_module;
12706   }
12707   
12708   /* When multiple interpeters are used, a module could have already been initialized in
12709        a different interpreter, but not yet have a pointer in this interpreter.
12710        In this case, we do not want to continue adding types... everything should be
12711        set up already */
12712   if (init == 0) return;
12713   
12714   /* Now work on filling in swig_module.types */
12715 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12716   printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: size %d\n", swig_module.size);
12717 #endif
12718   for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; ++i) {
12719     swig_type_info *type = 0;
12720     swig_type_info *ret;
12721     swig_cast_info *cast;
12722     
12723 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12724     printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: type %d %s\n", i, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
12725 #endif
12726     
12727     /* if there is another module already loaded */
12728     if (swig_module.next != &swig_module) {
12729       type = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module.next, &swig_module, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
12730     }
12731     if (type) {
12732       /* Overwrite clientdata field */
12733 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12734       printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found type %s\n", type->name);
12735 #endif
12736       if (swig_module.type_initial[i]->clientdata) {
12737         type->clientdata = swig_module.type_initial[i]->clientdata;
12738 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12739         printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found and overwrite type %s \n", type->name);
12740 #endif
12741       }
12742     } else {
12743       type = swig_module.type_initial[i];
12744     }
12745     
12746     /* Insert casting types */
12747     cast = swig_module.cast_initial[i];
12748     while (cast->type) {
12749       /* Don't need to add information already in the list */
12750       ret = 0;
12751 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12752       printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: look cast %s\n", cast->type->name);
12753 #endif
12754       if (swig_module.next != &swig_module) {
12755         ret = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module.next, &swig_module, cast->type->name);
12756 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12757         if (ret) printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found cast %s\n", ret->name);
12758 #endif
12759       }
12760       if (ret) {
12761         if (type == swig_module.type_initial[i]) {
12762 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12763           printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: skip old type %s\n", ret->name);
12764 #endif
12765           cast->type = ret;
12766           ret = 0;
12767         } else {
12768           /* Check for casting already in the list */
12769           swig_cast_info *ocast = SWIG_TypeCheck(ret->name, type);
12770 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12771           if (ocast) printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: skip old cast %s\n", ret->name);
12772 #endif
12773           if (!ocast) ret = 0;
12774         }
12775       }
12776       
12777       if (!ret) {
12778 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12779         printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: adding cast %s\n", cast->type->name);
12780 #endif
12781         if (type->cast) {
12782           type->cast->prev = cast;
12783           cast->next = type->cast;
12784         }
12785         type->cast = cast;
12786       }
12787       cast++;
12788     }
12789     /* Set entry in modules->types array equal to the type */
12790     swig_module.types[i] = type;
12791   }
12792   swig_module.types[i] = 0;
12793   
12794 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
12795   printf("**** SWIG_InitializeModule: Cast List ******\n");
12796   for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; ++i) {
12797     int j = 0;
12798     swig_cast_info *cast = swig_module.cast_initial[i];
12799     printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: type %d %s\n", i, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
12800     while (cast->type) {
12801       printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: cast type %s\n", cast->type->name);
12802       cast++;
12803       ++j;
12804     }
12805     printf("---- Total casts: %d\n",j);
12806   }
12807   printf("**** SWIG_InitializeModule: Cast List ******\n");
12808 #endif
12809 }
12810 
12811 /* This function will propagate the clientdata field of type to
12812 * any new swig_type_info structures that have been added into the list
12813 * of equivalent types.  It is like calling
12814 * SWIG_TypeClientData(type, clientdata) a second time.
12815 */
12816 SWIGRUNTIME void
12817 SWIG_PropagateClientData(void) {
12818   size_t i;
12819   swig_cast_info *equiv;
12820   static int init_run = 0;
12821   
12822   if (init_run) return;
12823   init_run = 1;
12824   
12825   for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; i++) {
12826     if (swig_module.types[i]->clientdata) {
12827       equiv = swig_module.types[i]->cast;
12828       while (equiv) {
12829         if (!equiv->converter) {
12830           if (equiv->type && !equiv->type->clientdata)
12831           SWIG_TypeClientData(equiv->type, swig_module.types[i]->clientdata);
12832         }
12833         equiv = equiv->next;
12834       }
12835     }
12836   }
12837 }
